product_name: Benefit Cosmetics Mini Cheek Stars Reunion Tour Palette
user_specs: ['Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Medium', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content:
This was the perfect set for me to try some new products and colors without committing to a full size. Turns out I love them all. Sometimes bronzers can look muddy/dirty on me, but the hoola is perfect. As is sugarbomb. Just a really great, universally flattering blush shade and I love how it transforms when you put georgia over the top. Warms it up a bit. My only complaint is that it doesn't wear very long, but I have yet to meet a blush that does on my skin.

product_name: Benefit Cosmetics Mini Cheek Stars Reunion Tour Palette
user_specs: ['Hair Condition Fine', 'Eye Color Brown', 'Hair color Black', 'Skin Tone Light', 'Skin Type Normal']
review_content: I really wanted to try the new shades. I was kind of disappointed in Georgia. The shade was so light and it didn’t really build up well. (And I’m light/medium skin tone) Sugar bomb really saved this palette. It’s such a nice pink rosy color. It gives your cheeks a nice healthy glow. And I have enough Hoola for lifetime. I would recommend save your money and just buy SugarBomb alone.

product_name: Benefit Cosmetics Mini Cheek Stars Reunion Tour Palette

review_content: Love the blushes, georgia smells so glorious and springy. Sugarbomb is pretty and subtle. Good price for minis. But Benefit, please Benefit, PUT SOMETHING BESIDES HOOLA IN EVERY PALETTE!!!! We all have 67 hoola bronzers!

review_title: Kind of upset, not gonna lie
review_content: Why hype about bringing back OG’s if you’re going to change them so much? I was so excited two of my favorites were back, only to be let down by the significant difference between old and new. I think the new ones are nice, just not the same. If you were looking forward to being able to restock old faves you will be disappointed.

product_name: Benefit Cosmetics Mini Cheek Stars Reunion Tour Palette
user_specs: ['Hair Condition Dry', 'Eye Color Green', 'Hair color Brunette', 'Skin Tone Medium', 'Skin Type Combination']
review_content:
It’s nice. The pigmentation is decent. I’m not a huge fan of Hoola but I like the other two colors. I wish they’d stop putting it in everything. I got a mini Dallas and I’ll probably try and swap out the hoola for Dallas and give hoola to a friend. I’ve had sugarbomb in the past and enjoy the nice pink pop. Georgia is pretty but subtle on light-medium skin. It’ll be a good travel palette for me if I’m able to swap the pans out without destroying the packaging.
